Shaolinq is a thoughtfully designed ORM and Linq provider for .NET
    
Use this package to add Shaolinq and out-of-the-box Postgres support (via the DotConnect ADO.NET Postgres provider).
    
Designed to perform super fast and be easy to use, Shaolinq's features also include:
    
- First class schema-first ORM with WYSIWYG data access and minipulation.
- First class LINQ support (not the basic kind you see in most other OSS projects).
- Single trip updating of objects.
- Support for Sqlite, MySql and Postgres.
- Automatic database creation and schema migration.
- Delete LINQ extension for batch server side deletes.
- Full support for server side date functions (Date.DayOfWeek etc).
- Easily extensible with a simple interface for adding support for other ADO.NET compatible databases.
- Open Source!
summary: A thoughtful ORM and Linq provider for .NET and Postgres (via the DotConnect Postgres provider)

Author's note: In recent years I was frustrated in attempts to find a public, documented and comprehensible managed library for manipulating ID3 tagged files. As the project Wiki page explains, in 2014 I reluctantly created this library to satisfy the requirement for an easy-to-use lightweight library that can manipulate all of the most commonly encountered features of the ID3 informal standards. Because the ID3 specification is so ridiculously complicated and because only a small subset of its features and versions are in common use, the NTagLite library is deliberately designed to be "lightweight" in the sense that it supports only the most common and practically useful subset of ID3 features. This subset is still a significant part of the full specification. The library can parse v2.2, v2.3 and v2.4 tags, but it only supports writing v2.3 tags.
summary: A lightweight library for manipulating ID3 tagged files.

A chart is a visual representation of data. It could be a bar chart, cross tab or a gauge. It could also just be a plain white number on a colored background.

      Traditionally, TARGIT Decision Suite has provided several standard charts, such as the ones mentioned above. After selecting measures and dimensions for a data object, switching between such standard charts has always been quick and easy.

      Should you wish to view your data as, say, a pie chart that looks like an actual real-world pie or as a bunch of green pulsating dots on an animated radar screen, you would not have been unable to do. Until now.

      Creating and using custom chart is made available for C# developers through our TARGIT Chart API NuGet package, free of charge.

      Through our chart API, a C#/Wpf developer can create custom data object types that literally look like anything you could think of, and effortlessly make them available to end users of TARGIT Decision Suite.
summary: An API for building custom charts for use in Targit Decision Suite

A chart is a visual representation of data. It could be a bar chart, cross tab or a gauge. It could also just be a plain white number on a colored background.

      Traditionally, TARGIT Decision Suite has provided several standard charts, such as the ones mentioned above. After selecting measures and dimensions for a data object, switching between such standard charts has always been quick and easy.

      Should you wish to view your data as, say, a pie chart that looks like an actual real-world pie or as a bunch of green pulsating dots on an animated radar screen, you would not have been unable to do. Until now.

      Creating and using custom chart is made available for C# developers through our TARGIT Chart API NuGet package, free of charge.

      Through our chart API, a C#/Wpf developer can create custom data object types that literally look like anything you could think of, and effortlessly make them available to end users of TARGIT Decision Suite.
summary: An API for building custom charts for use in Targit Decision Suite

description:
GroupDocs.Viewer for .NET is a powerful document viewer component that allows you to display over 50 document formats in your .NET applications. The viewer can both rasterize documents and convert them to SVG+HTML+CSS, delivering true-text high-fidelity rendering. 
Supported file formats include:

- Microsoft Office
- Microsoft Visio
- Microsoft Project
- Outlook documents
- PDF
- AutoCAD
- Image files (TIFF, JPG, BMP, GIF, TIFF, etc.)
and many more formats.

The GroupDocs.Viewer for .NET Library allows to get representation in html or image format for whole document, page-by-page or custom range of pages.

The product has the following key features:

- Native API, allowing all application functionality to be programmatically controlled
- Rendering document as html or image for each document type
- Set of predefined options for viewing in all modes, with proper default values
- Multiple render options - including text generation, watermarking among the others
- Abstract Storage API
- Abstract Cache API

For more details on the library, please visit GroupDocs website at:
http://groupdocs.com/dot-net/document-viewer-library

Note: The library comes up with some limitations in the evaluation mode. In order to test full features of GroupDocs.Viewer for .NET library, please request a free 30-day temporary license.
summary: GroupDocs.Viewer for .NET is a powerful document viewer component that allows you to display over 50 document formats.

      The package Simple.OData.Client contains libraries that can work with OData feeds that implement both V1-3 and V4 OData protocol.
      Packages Simple.OData.V3.Client and Simple.OData.V4.Client have smaller footprints and target V1-3 and V4 respectively.

The SDK supports producing native applications through the Xamarin framework

Shaolinq is a thoughtfully designed ORM and Linq provider for .NET
    
Use this package to add Shaolinq and out-of-the-box MySql support.
    
Designed to perform super fast and be easy to use, Shaolinq's features also include:
    
- First class schema-first ORM with WYSIWYG data access and minipulation.
- First class LINQ support (not the basic kind you see in most other OSS projects).
- Single trip updating of objects.
- Support for Sqlite, MySql and Postgres.
- Automatic database creation and schema migration.
- Delete LINQ extension for batch server side deletes.
- Full support for server side date functions (Date.DayOfWeek etc).
- Easily extensible with a simple interface for adding support for other ADO.NET compatible databases.
- Open Source!
summary: A thoughtful ORM and Linq provider for .NET and MySql

Author's note: In recent years I was frustrated in attempts to find a public, documented and comprehensible managed library for manipulating ID3 tagged files. As the project Wiki page explains, in 2014 I reluctantly created this library to satisfy the requirement for an easy-to-use lightweight library that can manipulate all of the most commonly encountered features of the ID3 informal standards. Because the ID3 specification is so ridiculously complicated and because only a small subset of its features and versions are in common use, the NTagLite library is deliberately designed to be "lightweight" in the sense that it supports only the most common and practically useful subset of ID3 features. This subset is still a significant part of the full specification. The library can parse v2.2, v2.3 and v2.4 tags, but it only supports writing v2.3 tags.
summary: A lightweight library for manipulating ID3 tagged files.

GroupDocs.Conversion for .NET is a universal document conversion library designed for easy integration into any .NET application. The library allows you to enhance your app with the capability to convert back and forth over 50 document and image file formats.

Keeping above in mind, GroupDocs.Conversion API is developed to make the life easier while working with Conversion. It is a very powerful and easy to use API that provides all basic Conversion operation for a number of file formats. API gets the file as an input and makes its Conversion accessible for the user. Now, its upto the user to perform any of his operations on this Conversion.

The product has the following key features:

- Converting document from all major file formats to all major file formats
- Native .NET API, allowing to third party developers to easy integrate GroupDocs.Conversion in their products
- Simple to use API - basically only one method with set of options for different formats.
- Abstract Storage API
- Abstract Cache API

Note: The library comes up with some limitations in the evaluation mode. In order to test full features of GroupDocs.Viewer for .NET library, please request a free 30-day temporary license.
summary: GroupDocs.Conversion for .NET is a universal document conversion library designed for easy integration into any .NET application.

description: A framework for building large scalable distributed applications with ease
summary:
A framework for building large scalable distributed applications with ease.
Main components:
Stardust.Nucleus: 
the stardust IOC container. 
This is a lightweight IOC containter that supports dependency injection and Object Lifecycle Management with an emphasis on performance.

Stardust.Interstellar: 
the stardust service and configuration framework. 
Provides support for centralized configuration and a unified programming model for integration technologies. Any service/integration technology has the same activation/usage providing an implementation agnostic abstraction. This also eases unit testing by allowing easy mocking of the service clients.

Stardust.Wormhole: 
The stardust type mapping framework. 
Stardust ships with a light weight type mapping and data merge tool.

Stardust.Clusters: 
A collection of helpers for common programming task like file parsing (supports separated files, old and new excel and simple xml, and allows registration of custom parsers). A generic file transfer tool that supports local disk, FTP and http in addition to custom implementations.
